    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for a medium-sized citrus fruit of several species, distinguished by having a rind with an orange color (reddish-yellow) and an acidic, juicy pulp that is sweeter than a lemon, grapefruit, or lime. The species most commonly intended by this term is Citrus sinensis.</Note_Text>
